        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 5:26PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Moore, or 16 miles southwest of Lewistown, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heath and Forestgrove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
